===Etymology===
{{wikipedia|yes and no}}
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|ya|lang=enm}}, {{term|ye|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|gea|ġēa|yes|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|ja|yes|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|yē|already|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|ja|lang=nl}}, German {{term|ja|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|ja|lang=sv}}. Related to existing English terms {{term|yes|lang=en}} and {{term|yea|lang=en}}.

